  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Kinetics of relativistic electrons passing through quasi-periodic fields</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-10</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We report a novel method for evaluating the energy spectrum of electrons emitting hard X-rays and gamma-rays in undulators and Compton sources. The method takes into account the quantum nature of recoils undergone by the electrons emitting high energy photons. The method is susceptible to evaluate a spectrum of electrons for the whole range of the emission rates per electron-pass through of the driving force, from much less than one emitted photon on average (Compton sources and short undulators) to many emitted photons (long undulators, relatively low-energy electrons). As shown in the former limiting case, the spectrum of electrons reflects the spectrum of emitted radiation whereas it is close to the Gaussian shape in the latter case. Limitation of coherency for the sources of high-energy electromagnetic radiation caused by recoils from emitted photons is also discussed.</subfield>
